The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE FILM

 (HBO, February 25, 11 pm) The Academy Awards countdown 

 on HBO airs Robert Zemeckis? Forrest Gump where Tom 

 Hanks plays a slow-witted country boy who embarks on a journey 

 of discovery through America of the 60s and 70s. The film 

 bagged four Oscars for Best Screenplay, Best Visual Effects, 

 Best Actor and Best Director. 

 THE CONCERT

 (Calcutta School of Music, February 21, 7 pm) The Indo-French 

 concert of nouvelle musique, hosted by Alliance Francaise 

 de Calcutta and Calcutta School of Music, features 

 vocals by Meeta Pandit, piano by Allie Delfau and percussions 

 from Gyan Singh. 

 THE DISPLAY

 (Sasha, 

 February 25 to March 6, 10 am to 7 pm) The exhibition-cum-sale 

 stocks handicrafts and gift items culled from across India 

 and Southeast Asia. The display also includes an array of 

 table and home linen, lamps, small furniture and ceramics. 




